OL,3,CDoctor raised concerns about Ian
OL,4,CPaterson seven years before his
OL,5,Csuspension
OL,7,FDr Andrew Stockdale, 70, a retired
OL,8,Foncologist, first raised concerns
OL,9,Fabout Paterson in 2003 when he
OL,10,Fbelieved the surgeon was carrying out
OL,11,Fincomplete mastectomies on patients
OL,12,Fwho were then being referred to him
OL,13,Ffor chemotherapy and radiotherapy
OL,14,Ftreatments.
OL,16,FHe described his contact with Paterson
OL,17,Fat multi-disciplinary team meetings as
OL,18,F"a particularly challenging
OL,19,Fenvironment."
