OL,3,CDoctor raised concerns about Ian
OL,4,CPaterson seven years before his
OL,5,Csuspension
OL,7,FSome women had mastectomies who did
OL,8,Fnot even have breast cancer.
OL,10,FAn inquiry, published in 2020,
OL,11,Fconcluded that Paterson, who was
OL,12,Femployed by the Heart of England NHS
OL,13,FFoundation Trust and practised in the
OL,14,Findependent sector at Spire Parkway
OL,15,Fand Spire Little Aston, was also
OL,16,Fcarrying out incomplete mastectomies
OL,17,Fat hospitals where he worked that left
OL,18,Fpatients at risk of cancer returning.
OL,20,FThey have become known as "cleavage-
OL,21,Fsparing" mastectomies.
